{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":458,"text":"I was told to come here\nand tell you all stories,"},{"time":3444,"text":"but what I'd like to do is instead\ntell you why I'm suspicious of stories,"},{"time":7657,"text":"why stories make me nervous."},{"time":10006,"text":"In fact, the more inspired\na story makes me feel,"},{"time":13125,"text":"very often, the more nervous I get."},{"time":15385,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":16515,"text":"So the best stories\nare often the trickiest ones."},{"time":19305,"text":"The good and bad things about stories\nis that they are a kind of filter."},{"time":22695,"text":"They take a lot of information,\nand they leave some of it out,"},{"time":25606,"text":"and they keep some of it in."},{"time":27350,"text":"But the thing about this filter is\nthat it always leaves the same things in."},{"time":31656,"text":"You're always left\nwith the same few simple stories."},{"time":34777,"text":"There is the old saying\nthat just about every story"},{"time":37173,"text":"can be summed up\nas \"a stranger came to town.\""},{"time":40614,"text":"There is a book by Christopher Booker,"},{"time":42466,"text":"where he claims there are really\njust seven types of stories."},{"time":45360,"text":"There is monster, rags to riches, quest,"},{"time":48030,"text":"voyage and return,\ncomedy, tragedy, rebirth."},{"time":52019,"text":"You don't have to agree\nwith that list exactly,"},{"time":54234,"text":"but the point is this:\nif you think in terms of stories,"},{"time":57564,"text":"you're telling yourself the same things\nover and over again."},{"time":61776,"text":"There was a study done,\nwe asked some people--"},{"time":70723,"text":"people were asked to describe their lives."},{"time":73933,"text":"When asked to describe their lives,"},{"time":75614,"text":"what is interesting\nis how few people said \"mess\"."},{"time":78861,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":80313,"text":"It's probably the best answer,\nI don't mean that in a bad way."},{"time":84355,"text":"\"Mess\" can be liberating,\n\"mess\" can be empowering,"},{"time":86768,"text":"\"mess\" can be a way\nof drawing upon multiple strengths."},{"time":90416,"text":"But what people wanted to say was,\n\"My life is a journey.\""},{"time":94784,"text":"51% wanted to turn\nhis or her life into a story."},{"time":99530,"text":"11% said, \"My life is a battle.\"\nAgain, that is a kind of story."},{"time":104368,"text":"8% said, \"My life is a novel.\"\n5% said, \"My life is a play.\""},{"time":108472,"text":"I don't think anyone said,\n\"My life is a reality TV show.\""},{"time":111798,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":112958,"text":"But again, we're imposing order\non the mess we observe,"},{"time":116653,"text":"and it's taking the same patterns,"},{"time":118283,"text":"and the thing is when something\nis in the form of a story,"},{"time":121349,"text":"often, we remember it when we shouldn't."},{"time":123853,"text":"So how many of you know the story"},{"time":125426,"text":"about George Washington\nand the cherry tree?"},{"time":128197,"text":"It's not obvious that is\nexactly what happened."},{"time":130467,"text":"The story of Paul Revere, it's not obvious\nthat that is exactly the way it happened."},{"time":135405,"text":"So again, we should be\nsuspicious of stories."},{"time":139135,"text":"We're biologically programmed\nto respond to them."},{"time":142468,"text":"They contain a lot of information.\nThey have social power."},{"time":145410,"text":"They connect us to other people."},{"time":147314,"text":"So they are like a candy that we're fed"},{"time":150039,"text":"when we consume political information,\nwhen we read novels."},{"time":153516,"text":"When we read non-fiction books,\nwe're really being fed stories."},{"time":156912,"text":"Non-fiction is, in a sense,\nthe new fiction."},{"time":159295,"text":"The book may happen to say true things,"},{"time":162120,"text":"but again, everything's taking\nthe same form of these stories."},{"time":166550,"text":"So what are the problems\nof relying too heavily on stories?"},{"time":170449,"text":"You view your life like this"},{"time":172346,"text":"instead of the mess\nthat it is or it ought to be."},{"time":175696,"text":"But more specifically,\nI think of a few major problems"},{"time":179763,"text":"when we think too much\nin terms of narrative."},{"time":183401,"text":"First, narratives tend to be too simple,"},{"time":185455,"text":"for the point of a narrative\nis to strip it away,"},{"time":187896,"text":"not just into 18 minutes,"},{"time":189502,"text":"but most narratives \nyou can present in a sentence or two."},{"time":192954,"text":"When you strip away detail,"},{"time":194815,"text":"you tend to tell stories\nin terms of good versus evil,"},{"time":198443,"text":"whether it's a story about your own life\nor a story about politics."},{"time":202604,"text":"I know some things actually are\ngood versus evil, we all know this, right?"},{"time":206458,"text":"But I think, as a general rule,"},{"time":207965,"text":"we're too inclined to tell\nthe good versus evil story."},{"time":212039,"text":"As a simple rule of thumb,"},{"time":213289,"text":"just imagine that every time\nyou're telling a good versus evil story,"},{"time":217539,"text":"you're basically lowering your IQ\nby ten points or more."},{"time":221715,"text":"If you just adopt that\nas a kind of inner mental habit,"},{"time":225052,"text":"it's, in my view, one way to get\na lot smarter pretty quickly."},{"time":228354,"text":"You don't have to read any books."},{"time":229973,"text":"Just imagine yourself pressing a button"},{"time":232028,"text":"every time you tell\nthe good versus evil story,"},{"time":234646,"text":"and by pressing that button,"},{"time":236223,"text":"you're lowering your IQ\nby ten points or more."},{"time":239283,"text":"Another set of stories that are popular--"},{"time":241284,"text":"if you know Oliver Stone's movies,\nor Michael Moore's movies,"},{"time":244651,"text":"you can't make a movie and say:\n\"It was all a big accident.\""},{"time":248253,"text":"No, it has to be a conspiracy,\npeople plotting together,"},{"time":252927,"text":"because in a story,\na story is about intention."},{"time":256307,"text":"A story is not about spontaneous order\nor complex human institutions"},{"time":260568,"text":"which are the product of human action,\nbut not of human design."},{"time":263748,"text":"No, a story is about evil people\nplotting together."},{"time":267835,"text":"So when you hear stories about plots,"},{"time":270473,"text":"or even stories about good people\nplotting things together,"},{"time":273493,"text":"just like when you're watching movies,"},{"time":275617,"text":"this, again, is reason to be suspicious."},{"time":278356,"text":"As a good rule of thumb, if you're asking:"},{"time":280367,"text":"\"When I hear a story, when should I\nbe especially suspicious?\""},{"time":283736,"text":"If you hear a story and you think:\n\"Wow, that would make a great movie!\""},{"time":288692,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":289774,"text":"That's when the \"uh-oh\" reaction\nshould pop in a bit more,"},{"time":293632,"text":"and you should start thinking in terms"},{"time":295566,"text":"of how the whole thing\nis maybe a bit of a mess."},{"time":299285,"text":"Another common story or storyline is\nthe claim that we \"have to get tough\"."},{"time":305233,"text":"You'll hear this in so many contexts."},{"time":307534,"text":"We have to get tough with the banks.\nWe had to get tough with the labor unions."},{"time":312801,"text":"We need to get tough\nwith some other country,"},{"time":314937,"text":"some foreign dictator,\nsomeone we're negotiating with."},{"time":318756,"text":"Again, the point is not\nagainst getting tough."},{"time":321105,"text":"Sometimes we should get tough."},{"time":322865,"text":"That we got tough with the Nazis\nwas a good thing."},{"time":326827,"text":"But this is again a story we fall back\nupon all too readily, all too quickly."},{"time":332181,"text":"When we don't really know\nwhy something happened,"},{"time":334478,"text":"we blame someone, and we say:\n\"We need to get tough with them!\""},{"time":338187,"text":"As if it had never occurred\nto your predecessor,"},{"time":340771,"text":"this idea of getting tough."},{"time":342989,"text":"I view it usually\nas a kind of mental laziness."},{"time":346095,"text":"It's a simple story you tell:\n\"We need to get tough,"},{"time":349377,"text":"we needed to get tough,\nwe will have to get tough.\""},{"time":352078,"text":"Usually, that is a kind of warning signal."},{"time":355623,"text":"Another kind of problem with stories is"},{"time":358784,"text":"you can only fit so many stories\ninto your mind at once,"},{"time":362206,"text":"or in the course of a day,\nor even over the course of a lifetime."},{"time":365268,"text":"So your stories are serving\ntoo many purposes."},{"time":368134,"text":"For instance, just to get\nout of bed in the morning,"},{"time":371027,"text":"you tell yourself the story"},{"time":373110,"text":"that your job is really important,\nwhat you're doing is really important"},{"time":376620,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":378456,"text":"and maybe it is, but I tell myself\nthat story even when it's not."},{"time":384694,"text":"And you know what? That story works."},{"time":386956,"text":"It gets me out of bed."},{"time":388610,"text":"It's a kind of self-deception,"},{"time":390968,"text":"but the problem comes\nwhen I need to change that story."},{"time":393575,"text":"The whole point of the story is\nthat I grab onto it and I hold it,"},{"time":397796,"text":"and it gets me out of bed."},{"time":399630,"text":"So when I'm really doing something\nthat is actually just a waste of time,"},{"time":403143,"text":"in my mess of a life,"},{"time":404958,"text":"I'm too tied into my story\nthat got me out of bed,"},{"time":409369,"text":"and ideally, I ought to have some\nvery complex story map in my mind,"},{"time":413107,"text":"you know, with combinatorials\nand a matrix of computation, and the like,"},{"time":416962,"text":"but that is not how stories work."},{"time":418868,"text":"Stories in order to work \nhave to be simple,"},{"time":420927,"text":"easily grasped, easily told\nto others, easily remembered."},{"time":424637,"text":"So stories will serve dual\nand conflicting purposes,"},{"time":427747,"text":"and very often they will lead us astray."},{"time":430636,"text":"I used to think I was\nwithin the camp of economists,"},{"time":433477,"text":"I was one of the good guys,\nand I was allied with other good guys,"},{"time":437537,"text":"and we were fighting\nthe ideas of the bad guys."},{"time":440666,"text":"I used to think that!"},{"time":442828,"text":"And probably, I was wrong."},{"time":444944,"text":"Maybe sometimes, I'm one of the good guys,"},{"time":446952,"text":"but on some issues, I finally realized:\n\"Hey, I wasn't one of the good guys.\""},{"time":451283,"text":"I'm not sure I was the bad guy\nin the sense of having evil intent,"},{"time":454705,"text":"but it was very hard for me\nto get away with that story."},{"time":459959,"text":"One interesting thing\nabout cognitive biases"},{"time":463753,"text":"is they are the subject\nof so many books these days."},{"time":466237,"text":"There's the Nudge book,\nthe Sway book, the Blink book,"},{"time":470750,"text":"like the one-title book,"},{"time":472508,"text":"all about the ways in which we screw up."},{"time":475681,"text":"And there are so many ways,"},{"time":477137,"text":"but what I find interesting\nis that none of these books identify"},{"time":480865,"text":"what, to me, is the single, central,\nmost important way we screw up,"},{"time":485067,"text":"and that is that we tell\nourselves too many stories,"},{"time":488762,"text":"or we are too easily seduced by stories."},{"time":491487,"text":"Why don't these books tell us that?"},{"time":493577,"text":"It's because the books themselves\nare all about stories."},{"time":497205,"text":"The more of these books you read,\nyou're learning about some of your biases,"},{"time":500983,"text":"but you're making some\nof your other biases essentially worse."},{"time":504920,"text":"So the books themselves\nare part of your cognitive bias."},{"time":508822,"text":"Often, people buy them\nas a kind of talisman, like:"},{"time":511376,"text":"\"I bought this book. I won't be\n'Predictably Irrational'.\""},{"time":515243,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":517903,"text":"It's like people want to hear the worst,"},{"time":519835,"text":"so psychologically, they can prepare\nfor it or defend against it."},{"time":523576,"text":"It's why there is\nsuch a market for pessimism."},{"time":526714,"text":"But to think that by buying the book\ngets you somewhere,"},{"time":529617,"text":"that's maybe the bigger fallacy."},{"time":531535,"text":"It's just like the evidence that shows\nthat the most dangerous people"},{"time":534797,"text":"are those who have been taught\nsome financial literacy."},{"time":537556,"text":"They're the ones who go out\nand make the worst mistakes."},{"time":540179,"text":"It's the people who realize\nthey don't know anything at all,"},{"time":543043,"text":"that end up doing pretty well."},{"time":545592,"text":"A third problem with stories"},{"time":547155,"text":"is that outsiders\nmanipulate us using stories,"},{"time":550533,"text":"and we all like to think advertising\nonly works on the other guy,"},{"time":553939,"text":"but, of course, that's not how it is,\nadvertising works on all of us."},{"time":558483,"text":"So if you're too attached to stories,"},{"time":560796,"text":"what will happen is people\nselling products come along,"},{"time":565008,"text":"and they will bundle\ntheir product with a story."},{"time":567386,"text":"You're like, \"Hey, a free story!\""},{"time":569033,"text":"And you end up buying the product,"},{"time":570678,"text":"because the product\nand the story go together."},{"time":572868,"text":"(Laugther)"},{"time":573906,"text":"If you think about how capitalism works,"},{"time":575845,"text":"there is a bias here."},{"time":577198,"text":"Let's consider two kinds\nof stories about cars."},{"time":580422,"text":"Story A is: \"Buy this car,"},{"time":583380,"text":"and you will have beautiful, romantic\npartners and a fascinating life.\""},{"time":586998,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":589398,"text":"There are a lot of people"},{"time":590628,"text":"who have a financial incentive\nto promote that story."},{"time":593123,"text":"But, say, the alternative story is:"},{"time":595671,"text":"\"You don't actually need a car\nas nice as your income would indicate."},{"time":599661,"text":"What you usually do is look\nat what your peers do and copy them."},{"time":603102,"text":"That is a good heuristic\nfor lots of problems,"},{"time":605246,"text":"but when it comes to cars,\njust buy a Toyota.\""},{"time":607569,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":609749,"text":"Maybe Toyota has an incentive there,"},{"time":611490,"text":"but even Toyota is making\nmore money off the luxury cars,"},{"time":614686,"text":"and less money off the cheaper cars."},{"time":616623,"text":"So if you think which set of stories\nyou end up hearing,"},{"time":619303,"text":"you end up hearing the glamor stories,\nthe seductive stories,"},{"time":622783,"text":"and again I'm telling you,\ndon't trust them."},{"time":625060,"text":"There are people using\nyour love of stories to manipulate you."},{"time":630331,"text":"Pull back and say:"},{"time":631501,"text":"\"What are the messages,"},{"time":632599,"text":"what are the stories\nthat no one has an incentive to tell?\""},{"time":635383,"text":"Start telling yourself those, and then see\nif any of your decisions change."},{"time":639970,"text":"That is one simple way."},{"time":641646,"text":"You can never get out of the pattern\nof thinking in terms of stories,"},{"time":645107,"text":"but you can improve the extent\nto which you think in stories,"},{"time":648743,"text":"and make some better decisions."},{"time":651517,"text":"So if I'm thinking about this talk,\nI'm wondering, of course,"},{"time":654671,"text":"what is it you take away from this talk?"},{"time":657298,"text":"What story do you take away\nfrom Tyler Cowen?"},{"time":661510,"text":"One story you might be\nlike the story of the quest."},{"time":664686,"text":"\"Tyler was a man on a quest."},{"time":667111,"text":"Tyler came here, and he told us\nnot to think so much in terms of stories.\""},{"time":673418,"text":"That would be a story\nyou could tell about this talk."},{"time":675908,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":677805,"text":"It would fit a pretty well-known pattern."},{"time":679787,"text":"You might remember it.\nYou could tell it to other people."},{"time":682676,"text":"\"This weird guy came, and he said,"},{"time":684396,"text":"'Don't think in terms of stories.\nLet me tell you what happened today!'\""},{"time":687796,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":688799,"text":"And you tell your story."},{"time":690330,"text":"(Laugther)"},{"time":693021,"text":"Another possibility is\nyou might tell a story of rebirth."},{"time":697833,"text":"You might say, \"I used to think\ntoo much in terms of stories"},{"time":702052,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":704794,"text":"but then I heard Tyler Cowen"},{"time":706912,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":707878,"text":"and now I think less in terms of stories!\""},{"time":711152,"text":"That too is a narrative you will remember,"},{"time":713952,"text":"you can tell to other people,\nand again, it may stick."},{"time":718463,"text":"You also could tell\na story of deep tragedy."},{"time":723086,"text":"\"This guy Tyler Cowen came"},{"time":725021,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":726271,"text":"and he told us not to think\nin terms of stories,"},{"time":728873,"text":"but all he could do was tell us stories"},{"time":730811,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":731877,"text":"about how other people think\ntoo much in terms of stories.\""},{"time":735838,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":738454,"text":"So, today, which is it?\nIs it like quest, rebirth, tragedy?"},{"time":743523,"text":"Or maybe some combination of the three?"},{"time":746626,"text":"I'm really not sure,\nand I'm not here to tell you"},{"time":749404,"text":"to burn your DVD player\nand throw out your Tolstoy."},{"time":753939,"text":"To think in terms of stories\nis fundamentally human."},{"time":758231,"text":"There is a Gabriel Garcia Marquez\nmemoir \"Living to Tell the Tale\""},{"time":764004,"text":"that we use memory in stories\nto make sense of what we've done,"},{"time":767465,"text":"to give meaning to our lives, to establish\nconnections with other people."},{"time":771958,"text":"None of this will go away,\nshould go away, or can go away."},{"time":776028,"text":"But again, as an economist,\nI'm thinking about life on the margin,"},{"time":781338,"text":"the extra decision."},{"time":782954,"text":"Should we think more in terms of stories,\nor less in terms of stories?"},{"time":787063,"text":"When we hear stories,\nshould we be more suspicious?"},{"time":791195,"text":"And what kind of stories\nshould we be suspicious of?"},{"time":793963,"text":"Again, I'm telling you it's the stories,\nvery often, that you like the most,"},{"time":798587,"text":"that you find the most rewarding,\nthe most inspiring."},{"time":802447,"text":"The stories that don't focus\non opportunity cost,"},{"time":806148,"text":"or the complex, unintended\nconsequences of human action,"},{"time":809969,"text":"because that very often\ndoes not make for a good story."},{"time":813863,"text":"So often a story is a story\nof triumph, a story of struggle;"},{"time":818513,"text":"there are opposing forces,\nwhich are either evil or ignorant;"},{"time":823020,"text":"there is a person on a quest,\nsomeone making a voyage,"},{"time":826310,"text":"and a stranger coming to town."},{"time":829049,"text":"And those are your categories,\nbut don't let them make you too happy."},{"time":834870,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":837419,"text":"As an alternative,"},{"time":839954,"text":"at the margin\n- again, no burning of Tolstoy -"},{"time":843283,"text":"but just be a little more messy."},{"time":846739,"text":"If I actually had to live those journeys,\nand quests, and battles,"},{"time":851226,"text":"that would be so oppressive to me!"},{"time":853263,"text":"It's like, my goodness,\ncan't I just have my life"},{"time":856000,"text":"in its messy, ordinary \n- I hesitate to use the word - glory"},{"time":859645,"text":"but that it's fun for me?"},{"time":861655,"text":"Do I really have to follow\nsome kind of narrative?"},{"time":864008,"text":"Can't I just live?"},{"time":865780,"text":"So be more comfortable with messy."},{"time":869456,"text":"Be more comfortable with agnostic,"},{"time":872176,"text":"and I mean this about the things\nthat make you feel good."},{"time":874871,"text":"It's so easy to pick out\na few areas to be agnostic in,"},{"time":877644,"text":"and then feel good about it,"},{"time":878997,"text":"like, \"I am agnostic\nabout religion, or politics.\""},{"time":882828,"text":"It's a kind of portfolio move you make\nto be more dogmatic elsewhere, right?"},{"time":887040,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":889220,"text":"Sometimes,"},{"time":890290,"text":"the most intellectually trustworthy people\nare the ones who pick one area,"},{"time":893836,"text":"and they are totally dogmatic in that,\nso pig-headedly unreasonable,"},{"time":897028,"text":"that you think,\n\"How can they possibly believe that?\""},{"time":899678,"text":"But it soaks up their stubbornness,"},{"time":904170,"text":"and then, on other things,\nthey can be pretty open-minded."},{"time":907340,"text":"So don't fall into the trap of thinking\nbecause you're agnostic on some things,"},{"time":911079,"text":"that you're being fundamentally reasonable"},{"time":913092,"text":"about your self-deception, your stories,\nand your open-mindedness."},{"time":916192,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":918889,"text":"[Think about] this idea of hovering,\nof epistemological hovering,"},{"time":922756,"text":"and messiness, and incompleteness,"},{"time":926413,"text":"[and how] not everything \nties up into a neat bow,"},{"time":929049,"text":"and you're really not on a journey here."},{"time":931879,"text":"You're here for some\nmessy reason or reasons,"},{"time":934746,"text":"and maybe you don't know what it is,\nand maybe I don't know what it is,"},{"time":938833,"text":"but anyway, I'm happy to be invited,\nand thank you all for listening."},{"time":942113,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":943111,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}